Class ArrayHash<KEY,VALUE>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    KEY - key type

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<KEY,VALUE>

    public final class ArrayHash<KEY,VALUE>
extends java.util.HashMap<KEY,VALUE>
    An extension of the HashMap that also preservers the insertion order. This implementation allows for fast random access to the data as well as sequential access via an internal ArrayList. As this structure is based on a HashMap, it only keeps unique data values.
